Elliott Lewis (radio) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elliott_Lewis_(radio) 0 Elliott Lewis (November 28, 1917 – May 23, 1990) was active during the Golden Age of Radio as an actor, producer and director, proficient in both comedy and drama. These talents earned him the nickname "Mr. Radio".
